### JavaScript: Redirect Console Output to HTML Textarea

Source: https://github.com/dexie/dexie.js/blob/master/samples/open-existing-db/dump-databases.html

This JavaScript code defines a custom `Console` object that overrides the default `window.console` behavior. It redirects all `console.log` and `console.error` messages to a dynamically created `<textarea>` element, which is then appended to a specified HTML element (`consoleArea`). This allows users to view console output directly on the web page, useful for in-browser debugging or demonstrations without opening developer tools.

```JavaScript
function Console() {
  this.textarea = document.createElement('textarea');
  this.log = function (txt, type) {
    if (type) this.textarea.value += type + " ";
    this.textarea.value += txt + "\n";
  }
  this.error = function (txt) {
    this.log(txt, "ERROR!");
  }
}
window.console = new Console();
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
  document.getElementById('consoleArea').appendChild(console.textarea);
});
```

