### db.on('changes') Event

Source: https://github.com/dexie/dexie.js/blob/master/addons/Dexie.Observable/README.md

Details the `db.on('changes')` event, which allows subscribing to all database modifications, regardless of whether they originate locally or from other browser windows. It specifies the parameters passed to the callback function upon event trigger.

```APIDOC
db.on('changes') event:
  Description: Subscribe to any database changes no matter if they occur locally or in other browser window.
  Parameters:
    - changes: Array<DatabaseChange>
      Description: Array of changes that have occured in database (locally or in other window) since last time event was triggered, or the time of starting subscribing to changes.
    - partial: Boolean
      Description: True in case the array does not contain all changes. In this case, your callback will soon be called again with the additional changes and partial=false when all changes are delivered.
```

