### JavaScript Representation of Tree Node Ranges

Source: https://github.com/dexie/dexie.js/blob/master/test/rebalance.md

This snippet shows an array of JavaScript objects, where each object defines a numerical range using 'from' and 'to' properties. Accompanying comments illustrate how these ranges might be organized within a tree structure, highlighting specific node relationships and a case where left and right child nodes are identical.

```js
  { from: 63, to: 71 },  // 0. Tree: [63-71]
  { from: 99, to: 102 }, // 1. Tree: [63-71]
                         //      (null)  [99-102]
  { from: 90, to: 92 },  // 2. Tree: [99-102]
                         //       [63-71]  (null)
                         //    [90-92] [90-92]
                         // WOW: Here both left and right leafs are the same node!
```

